        <input type="text" name="code" placeholder="Enter code" required>
        <input type="submit" value="Verify">
    </form>
</div>
</body>
</html>

ruby for email authentication
📤 Ruby Script to Send Email Using Gmail SMTP
ruby
Copy
Edit
# main.rb

require 'mail'

# Set up SMTP settings
Mail.defaults do
  delivery_method :smtp, {
    address:              'smtp.gmail.com',
    port:                 587,
    user_name:            'your_email@gmail.com',        # 👈 your Gmail address
    password:             'your_app_password_here',      # 👈 your generated app password
    authentication:       :login,
    enable_starttls_auto: true
  }
end

# Define the email message
message = Mail.new do
  from    'your_email@gmail.com'       # 👈 same as user_name above
  to      'receiver@example.com'       # 👈 receiver's email
  subject 'Hello from Ruby!'
  body    'This is a test email sent from a Ruby script using Gmail SMTP.'
end

# Send the email
message.deliver!

puts "✅ Email sent successfully!"
✅ Steps to Set Up Gmail (to use in script)
🔐 1. Enable 2-Step Verification (if not already enabled):
Go to: https://myaccount.google.com

Click "Security" on the left.

Under "Signing in to Google", enable 2-Step Verification.

🔑 2. Create an App Password
In the Security section, search “App Passwords” or go to: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords

Select App: Mail, Device: Other (Custom name) → enter something like “RubyScript”

Click Generate

Copy the 16-character app password (no spaces)

🔐 IMPORTANT: This is your "email password" for the Ruby script — not your actual Gmail password!

💻 Running the Script
🧪 Option 1: On Replit
Go to https://replit.com

Click Create Repl

Choose "Ruby" as the language

Paste the full script into main.rb

Open the Shell tab and run:

css
Copy
Edit
gem install mail
ruby main.rb
🧪 Option 2: Locally on Your Computer
Make sure you have Ruby installed (ruby -v)

Create a file called main.rb and paste the script above

Open terminal and run:

bash
Copy
Edit
gem install mail
ruby main.rb
✅ Recap of Full Steps

Step	Action
1	Enable 2-Step Verification on your Gmail
2	Generate an App Password
3	Paste password in Ruby script
4	Replace sender & receiver emails
5	Install mail gem (gem install mail)
6	Run script using ruby main.rb
7	✅ Done — Email sent!



